{
  "texts": [
    "Bench, as introduced by Arora et al. (2023, pp. 4-9), is a benchmark across various domains, notably in chemistry.",
    "Comprising 515 instances, of which 156 are in the chemistry domain, this benchmark consists of exam questions categorized by the expected answers, including multiple-choice, integer, and numeric responses.",
    "In Fig. 2, an example from JEEBench is provided.",
    "Bench serves as a specialized benchmark within the educational technology landscape, specifically designed to assess the abilities of LLMs against the rigorous standards of Joint Entrance Examination (JEE) questions, which are pivotal in engineering education.",
    "This collection of tasks, meticulously derived from past JEE questions, provides a unique insight into how well LLMs can tackle high-stakes, conceptually demanding problems in physics, chemistry, and mathematics."
  ]
}